      "image": "#"
    },
    "options": [],
    "correct_answer": "$PQ=13$ units",
    "solution": {
      "text": "Use coordinates of points and distance formula.",
      "image": "#"
    },
    "solution_steps": [
      "Step 1: Since point $P$ lies on the x-axis with abscissa $5$,",
      "$P=(5,0)$",
      "Step 2: Since point $Q$ lies on the y-axis with ordinate $-12$,",
      "$Q=(0,-12)$",
      "Step 3: Using the distance formula:",
      "$d=\\sqrt{(x_2-x_1)^2+(y_2-y_1)^2}$",
      "Step 4: Substitute the values:",
      "$PQ=\\sqrt{(0-5)^2+(-12-0)^2}$",
      "$=\\sqrt{(-5)^2+(-12)^2}$",
      "$=\\sqrt{25+144}$",
      "$=\\sqrt{169}$",
      "$=13$",
      "Final Answer: Therefore, the distance $PQ=13$ units."
    ]
